USA: Repetition is the Mother of Wisdom
It is comic that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the dumbest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, eagerly expected, it was demonstrated that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only is the same text used several times as in Iraq, but it has not hesitated to use the title of the Bush Declaration of January 2007 for its own statement: "A new way forward."
He was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
In the following months, however, they showed that the Bush strategy, based on the recommendations of camp captains, was the only possible and successful one, so that today there is no talk of Iraq in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, yet objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes that the miracle will be repeated.
The camp captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan operation, Stanley McCristal. He, even in spite of traditional subordinate relations, subjected the undecided gunmen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He asked for 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he tricked the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he himself had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing the troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and finalize this procedure in three years. Obama's entire doctrine generated more questions than he offered.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing their boss every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. Following it will remain patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confused relationships, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capacity of action", a minimal objective of the entire operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocking for his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing of reality, can believe that the military sent to war to "go home soon," will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and increased sanctions have no effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to look for answers precisely when, according to Obama, America initiates the triumphal withdrawal of the troops from Afghanistan.
Each solution, however, will mean a dramatic setback to the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for the presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
